1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,920
[Lucas]<i> I saw you in an alley in Manila.</i>

2
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:06,214
<i>I left money in your hand.</i>

3
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:07,716
<i>Back when I had nothing,</i>

4
00:00:07,799 --> 00:00:10,010
<i>someone gave me 50 pesos.</i>

5
00:00:10,093 --> 00:00:11,636
<i>I didn't see who he was.</i>

6
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,263
<i>He was the one who saved my life.</i>

7
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:17,642
<i>I kept calling you last night.</i>

8
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:19,310
<i>You were with Erica.</i>

9
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:23,231
<i>She was just kind</i>
<i>enough to take me to my hotel.</i>

10
00:00:23,314 --> 00:00:26,109
<i>You know that I'm here whenever</i>
<i>you need someone to talk to, right?</i>

11
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,737
<i>Talking with you means,</i>
<i>I get to talk to someone, too.</i>

12
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,031
<i>I need that now, Lucas.</i>

13
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:33,074
<i>Someone to hold on to.</i>

14
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,451
<i>After what I've heard,</i>

15
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,578
<i>I started to question everything, Beth.</i>

16
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:37,746
<i>Do you still love me?</i>

17
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:42,625
<i>Do you still mourn the dreams</i>
<i>you had to give up on every night?</i>

18
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:44,252
<i>Maybe I'll be okay eventually.</i>

19
00:00:44,335 --> 00:00:45,378
<i>- Edward.</i>
<i>- Edward.</i>

20
00:00:45,462 --> 00:00:48,590
<i>The delivery of donations</i>
<i>for healing mass at Santa Fe,</i>

21
00:00:48,673 --> 00:00:50,008
<i>we'll take care of them.</i>

22
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,343
<i>We're just worried about you and Christina</i>

23
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:54,012
<i>after what happened to you.</i>

24
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:55,180
<i>That's nothing to me.</i>

25
00:00:55,263 --> 00:00:57,474
<i>Really, this was my vow.</i>

26
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,893
<i>Shouldn't we still continue our vows</i>

27
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,519
<i>even when faced with hardship?</i>

28
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:03,730
<i>We've got a buffet of criminal charges.</i>

29
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:08,902
<i>And as for Anton, he will be served</i>
<i>a full-course meal of accountability.</i>

30
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:11,821
<i>Do not say anything</i>
<i>aggressive against the women.</i>

31
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,448
<i>If we control the narrative,</i>

32
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,742
<i>we show the court</i>
<i>there's a reasonable doubt.</i>

33
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:16,826
<i>That's easy.</i>

34
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:21,081
<i>[Alba] Now, let's make sure</i>
<i>Anton Montenegro regrets,</i>

35
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:23,416
<i>that he touched any of you.</i>

36
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:26,085
I want you to be prepared

37
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:28,838
because their counter-offensive
is going to be brutal.

38
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:30,548
Their strategy…

39
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,301
Attempted homicide for you, Alice.

40
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:38,264
And they will argue
that that bottle strike was a calculated

41
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,809
and disproportionate act of violence

42
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:43,353
They will try to pressure you, Alice.

43
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:46,147
And they will even try
to paint this whole incident

44
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:50,944
as a luring and gang up
orchestrated by Mel and Erica.

45
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:56,282
[dramatic music playing]

46
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,867
[exhales deeply] Don't worry.

47
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:00,370
It's a desperate move.

48
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:02,497
We have a lot of witnesses.

49
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,916
The fact that he was
choking me before you hit him.

50
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:07,877
It's a clear act of saving a life.

51
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,504
We stick to our truth.

52
00:02:10,046 --> 00:02:14,634
They will use their PR
team to spin sympathy online.

53
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:15,760
Ah…

54
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:19,222
Poor Anton Montenegro.

55
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:21,015
Poor husband.

56
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:23,685
It's a narcissist rebrand
that has been used for years.

57
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:25,186
But people are still buying it.

58
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,855
And unfortunately,

59
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:29,023
a lot of them are women.

60
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:31,025
[Erica] Then let's strike first.

61
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:33,903
Let's reach out to his other victims.

62
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:36,114
Jo, right?

63
00:02:36,906 --> 00:02:39,117
Do you think she will help you?

64
00:02:40,326 --> 00:02:42,787
Yes. I think so.

65
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:48,877
Good. The louder the truth,
the smaller his lies sound.

66
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:52,380
And you two, no reposts

67
00:02:52,463 --> 00:02:54,048
and no cryptic posts.

68
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:55,842
Because, trust me, darlings,

69
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:59,387
screenshots age worse than bruises.

70
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:01,431
[dramatic music continues]

71
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:02,807
Listen.

72
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,602
I've seen way too many women walk in here,

73
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,353
anxious and scared.

74
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:09,898
But the four of you,

75
00:03:09,981 --> 00:03:12,609
you come in here, already roaring.

76
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:16,029
I'm confident that we will win.

77
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:20,199
But what you are doing here, it matters.

78
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:22,827
Because you are not
just standing up for yourselves.

79
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:26,289
You are fighting for
women who were abused,

80
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:30,293
afraid, silenced, and
who can't find the courage to speak up.

81
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:33,838
Do you know what you are giving them?

82
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,424
Hope.

83
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:41,387
[dramatic music swells]

84
00:03:47,435 --> 00:03:54,234
[theme music playing]

85
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:12,395
Sweetheart.

86
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:14,188
I'm going to head out later, okay?

87
00:05:15,606 --> 00:05:16,941
Just for the day.

88
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:20,737
[chuckles softly]
There's something I just have to do.

89
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:25,408
[uneasy music playing]

90
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:33,249
[door creaks]

91
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,834
Good morning.

92
00:05:34,917 --> 00:05:36,878
- [Althea] Uncle.
- [Edward] Althea.

93
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:41,090
[Althea] Morning, Christina.

94
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:44,469
I've been so worried about you.

95
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:45,928
How are you two?

96
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:48,056
[Edward chuckles softly]

97
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:50,141
We're all right, see?

98
00:05:50,224 --> 00:05:52,727
Like what I told you on the phone.

99
00:05:53,394 --> 00:05:55,521
You are the one I should be asking.

100
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:57,440
I'm fine.

101
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,361
Althea…

102
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,906
Are you sure…

103
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:08,284
that it's okay for
you to look after Christina?

104
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:11,621
I can understand if
you're scared about going--

105
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:13,956
It's fine with me, Uncle.

106
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,375
There are police officers outside,

107
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:19,629
and your neighbors
are looking after you, too.

108
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:22,340
He'd be stupid to come back here, right?

109
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:23,633
[uneasy music playing]

110
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,385
Besides, I'd be more at ease

111
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:28,763
if I were the one
looking after Miss Christina.

112
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,433
What did your parents say?

113
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,393
Uh…

114
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:37,647
Well, we had a long conversation.

115
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:40,358
But I was able to convince my mother.

116
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:42,860
Don't worry, Uncle.

117
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,779
Mama will be here later,

118
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:48,407
and Papa will pick us up
so we can go back home together.

119
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:51,119
[music becomes gentle]

120
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,453
[exhales deeply]

121
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,956
Thank you very much, Althea.

122
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,875
You know that you're
the only one I can trust

123
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,545
to look after your Aunt Christina.

124
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:04,298
I don't get worried even when I leave.

125
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,717
It's really a good thing…

126
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,512
that we're all okay.

127
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:13,266
And if Edong tries to come back,

128
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,268
at least we're ready, right?

129
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:18,354
You really like your sister.

130
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:20,773
Brave.

131
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:25,319
[gentle music continues, fades]

132
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,447
- [birds chirping]
- [doorbell dings]

133
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:34,912
[suspenseful music playing]

134
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:36,622
[doorbell dings]

135
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,835
[music fades]

136
00:07:40,918 --> 00:07:43,129
Mel, I'll just go and meet Marco.

137
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:46,257
Lucas is still watching Travis's house.

138
00:07:46,632 --> 00:07:48,676
Don't go out without security.

139
00:07:55,349 --> 00:07:57,143
I used to have a crush on Lucas.

140
00:07:58,227 --> 00:08:03,316
[melancholic music playing]

141
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,238
Back in high school.

142
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,660
He was always so quiet.

143
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:16,204
But solid.

144
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:19,165
Like, no matter what happened,

145
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,419
he'd be able to handle it.

146
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,965
I never really acted on it

147
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:30,635
because I knew my
parents would never like him.

148
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,516
That's why I was so surprised when…

149
00:08:37,808 --> 00:08:39,393
when I found out that you got together.

150
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:44,148
I didn't even know
that you knew each other.

151
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:47,693
But you didn't say anything at the time.

152
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:51,364
[melancholic music continues]

153
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:53,157
[young Erica]
<i>I will introduce you to Lucas.</i>

154
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,952
<i>I promise you will see that he's okay.</i>

155
00:08:57,453 --> 00:08:59,330
[Mel] A lot of things happened back then.

156
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:04,961
And you and Lucas barely
even had the chance to be a couple.

157
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:09,674
[melancholic music continues]

158
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:18,849
But, why are you telling me this now?

159
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,981
I've been meaning
to tell you for a long time, Erica.

160
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:27,567
I'm sure you're wondering

161
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:30,778
how he and I came to have an affair.

162
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:33,573
It didn't come out of nothing.

163
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:36,409
When I met Lucas again,

164
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:39,036
he knew what I was going through…

165
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:41,289
with Anton.

166
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:45,376
That just brought
back old feelings, you know?

167
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,046
Anyway,

168
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:51,340
now that I've told you,

169
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:53,009
it's off my chest.

170
00:09:55,761 --> 00:10:00,016
[melancholic music continues]

171
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:01,851
I don't own him, Mel.

172
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:07,690
And I have no right
to judge what happened to you before.

173
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,611
Besides, that's done.

174
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,699
But I don't want it to be over.

175
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:21,329
[melancholic music continues]

176
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,712
[music fades]

177
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,964
[Isla] What do you feel, Alice?

178
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:34,884
[Alice sighs]

179
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:37,928
I'm scared.

180
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:42,767
[unsettling music playing]

181
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:43,893
It's like…

182
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,395
It's all happening at the same time.

183
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,481
Anton…

184
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,775
Edong…

185
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:53,527
My memories…

186
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:56,489
What you're feeling is normal.

187
00:10:57,865 --> 00:10:58,866
It's not easy.

188
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:01,619
But you don't have to face this alone.

189
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:04,330
Scott would be a great support for you.

190
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:05,998
I know…

191
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,127
But Seth…

192
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:15,091
Seth's already been through so much.

193
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:17,927
And after what happened with Edong…

194
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:21,222
I don't want him
to become more traumatized.

195
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:24,058
Scott promised me that…

196
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:27,436
He'll make sure Seth
gets therapy back home.

197
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:31,732
We won't let him--

198
00:11:32,566 --> 00:11:33,901
become like me.

199
00:11:33,984 --> 00:11:37,405
[unsettling music swells]

200
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,824
You know, before…

201
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,743
I thought healing meant…

202
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:45,204
forgetting the past.

203
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:47,665
But now I know,

204
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:50,126
I have to face it.

205
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:52,920
Reclaim it.

206
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:55,423
Every,

207
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,007
painful,

208
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,384
bit of it.

209
00:11:58,467 --> 00:11:59,885
[music fades]

210
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,305
Alice, can you hear yourself?

211
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:06,016
That's strength.

212
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,518
[hopeful music playing]

213
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:11,230
Yes, you're scared
and overwhelmed right now.

214
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:16,735
But even the strongest, the bravest,

215
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,404
also get scared.

216
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,365
What's important is,

217
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:24,535
you're not running
away from your past anymore.

218
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:26,745
You're now facing it.

219
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:28,581
Finally.

220
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:30,624
Eyes open.

221
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,502
You've come a long way.

222
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:39,633
[hopeful music swells]

223
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:46,140
- [music fades]
- [birds chirping]

224
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,396
[Marco sighs heavily]

225
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:55,774
Looks like Kyle's mother isn't there.

226
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:59,069
I've been waiting for her since earlier.

227
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,324
I wonder what's going
through Oslo's mind right now.

228
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:07,495
He can't escape anymore.
He's in the videos.

229
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:11,999
But he's still not saying anything.
[sighs heavily]

230
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,503
Laurence Kyo hasn't woken up.

231
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:18,839
He probably thinks
his boss would still recover

232
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:21,050
and be discharged from the hospital.

233
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:25,304
He knows Laurence is
more dangerous than the police.

234
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:30,267
He'd rather go to jail than blame Kyo.

235
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:33,145
Lucas is lucky.

236
00:13:34,605 --> 00:13:37,441
He was involved in
Kyo's illegal operation.

237
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,902
But Steve came to his rescue.

238
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,281
You too. You saved him.

239
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:48,994
[Erica sighs]

240
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:52,540
We both know
he didn't want that to happen.

241
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:55,876
And all the evidence
we needed came from him.

242
00:13:56,794 --> 00:14:00,714
That's how Oslo got caught,
and the women's bodies were found.

243
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:03,008
You know you don't
have to spend your whole life

244
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:05,511
being guilty for what
happened to those brothers, Erica.

245
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:09,807
He was the fifty pesos.

246
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:15,145
[pensive music playing]

247
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:18,023
I told you about it before, right?

248
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:22,069
When I first went to Manila,
I had a really hard time.

249
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,447
Until one day,

250
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:29,285
I suddenly dropped
like garbage in an alley.

251
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,664
I was helpless that time.

252
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:38,168
[pensive music continues]

253
00:14:38,252 --> 00:14:39,420
When I woke up…

254
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:43,340
I had fifty pesos in my hand.

255
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:50,264
That money gave me
the strength to continue living.

256
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:54,810
[pensive music continues]

257
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,020
That was him.

258
00:14:58,230 --> 00:14:59,315
He saw me.

259
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,192
He was the one who gave the money.

260
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,905
Are you sure he didn't just say that

261
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:08,824
because he knew
that's what you wanted to hear?

262
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:14,121
I didn't even ask him about that.

263
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:16,749
He was drunk.

264
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:20,836
He couldn't even remember saying it to me.

265
00:15:22,504 --> 00:15:27,885
[pensive music continues]

266
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:39,188
[Erica] <i>We're the same.</i>

267
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,606
[Erica grunts]

268
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:43,901
[Erica] <i>We left</i>
<i>Amurao to start anew in Manila.</i>

269
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,988
<i>I know how hard that is.</i>

270
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,533
[Erica] <i>But we both did it.</i>

271
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:55,704
[pensive music continues]

272
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:02,670
[Erica] Alice…

273
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:04,672
thinks we…

274
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,550
We still have a connection.

275
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:12,429
[pensive music continues]

276
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:15,724
[music fades]

277
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,393
[Beth] We have to be prepared.

278
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,728
I'm sure that because of the case,

279
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,981
a lot of people will
gossip about me again.

280
00:16:22,606 --> 00:16:24,108
You can get involved in that.

281
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:27,611
There will probably be
bashers from Amurao again.

282
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,655
They'll throw all kinds of comments

283
00:16:29,738 --> 00:16:31,240
even though
they don't really know anything,

284
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:36,370
especially since Anton
comes from a prominent family.

285
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,288
[breaths heavily]

286
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:43,961
Uh… But of course,
that might not even happen.

287
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:47,506
The trolls might just ignore me.

288
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:49,591
[mumbling nervously]

289
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:51,135
Who am I anyway?

290
00:16:52,386 --> 00:16:54,388
[voice breaking] I'm just nobody, right?

291
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,224
[chuckles awkwardly]

292
00:16:57,307 --> 00:17:00,644
[somber music playing]

293
00:17:00,728 --> 00:17:05,107
You're far from being
"just nobody" to us, Ma.

294
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:09,486
And this life we have…

295
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:12,698
it isn't just "nothing," either.

296
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:16,702
[chair scrapes]

297
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:21,373
[somber music continues]

298
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:26,879
[music fades]

299
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:29,173
[woman] We can't thank you enough, Edward.

300
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:32,426
You could have
given all of this to Amurao,

301
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:34,928
- but you never forgot about us.
- [Edward chuckles]

302
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:38,599
She's right, Mister Edward.
Thank you so much.

303
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:40,309
This really helps us a lot.

304
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:41,727
It's nothing, really.

305
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:44,480
Besides, you're not strangers to me.

306
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:48,776
In the end,
it's us who should help one another.

307
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:50,235
[women giggling]

308
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:51,820
Why don't you stay for dinner?

309
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,739
We have a bit of food prepared.

310
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:56,492
It's the least we can do for you.

311
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:57,826
[women giggling]

312
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:03,207
Oh, that's very kind, Sister,
but Christina's waiting for me.

313
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:05,667
- You know how she is.
- [all chuckle]

314
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:08,045
Christina's really lucky to have you.

315
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:11,215
You're not just kind,
you're a loving husband, too.

316
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:12,382
[nun giggles]

317
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:16,261
I wish I could all find
someone like Mister Edward.

318
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:19,431
[all chuckle]

319
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:29,274
Chloe, what's the problem?

320
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,907
[sobs softly]

321
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:39,493
I heard you and Papa arguing.

322
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:42,955
[Chloe's breath quivers]

323
00:18:43,038 --> 00:18:46,375
I know you're not happy living here…

324
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,377
with us.

325
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:50,420
Chloe, that's not true.

326
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:52,881
Then why couldn't you answer Papa

327
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:55,759
when he asked if you'd still choose us?

328
00:18:55,843 --> 00:18:59,263
- [somber music playing]
- [Chloe sobbing softly]

329
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:01,140
Don't you love me anymore, Ma?

330
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:06,228
Do you regret having me as your child?

331
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:08,814
Chloe, no.

332
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:14,736
I will never, ever regret having you.

333
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,864
- [sniffles]
- [Beth] Okay?

334
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:20,033
I love you so much, okay?

335
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:22,286
I'm so proud of you.

336
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:26,248
I love you and your Papa so, so much.

337
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:30,836
You are my life.

338
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,339
You see, Ma…

339
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:35,716
[sniffles]

340
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:41,096
…ever since Edong showed up,
everything has changed.

341
00:19:42,472 --> 00:19:43,599
[sniffles]

342
00:19:43,682 --> 00:19:48,020
I'm not really afraid
that he'll go after me again

343
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:50,230
or hurt me.

344
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:53,150
What scares me more is that

345
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:57,404
he could be
the reason you and Papa separate,

346
00:19:57,821 --> 00:20:00,574
and why our family might fall apart.

347
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:04,745
[somber music continues]

348
00:20:05,704 --> 00:20:07,998
[both sob softly]

349
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:19,593
[somber music continues]

350
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:30,020
[music fades]

351
00:20:30,103 --> 00:20:34,066
[women crying on TV]

352
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:40,864
- [emotional music playing on TV]
- [crying continues]

353
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,913
[women continue crying]

354
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,919
[woman 1 speaking indistinctly]

355
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,384
[TV noises fade]

356
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:02,678
Ma'am Christina…

357
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:06,515
You startled me.

358
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:12,688
You know what just
happened with Edong, right?

359
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:15,691
[TV continues indistinctly in background]

360
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,150
[softly] There…

361
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,528
[ominous music playing]

362
00:21:19,611 --> 00:21:20,946
There…

363
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:24,199
- [ominous music playing]
- [woman on TV continues]

364
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:25,575
There…

365
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,370
There…

366
00:21:30,163 --> 00:21:31,415
There…

367
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:34,126
[ominous music continues]

368
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:35,377
[Christina] There…

369
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:38,588
There…

370
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:41,216
There…

371
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:48,724
[ominous music intensifies]

372
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:59,860
[ominous music intensifies]

373
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:08,493
[ominous music crescendos]

374
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:12,789
<i>Kyle isn't in the U.S., is he?</i>
<i>He's here. Inside.</i>

375
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:14,541
<i>What you're doing is harassment.</i>

376
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:17,627
<i>Show your face</i>
<i>again and I'll call the police!</i>

377
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:18,670
[gunshot]

378
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:21,506
<i>- Marco!</i>
<i>- What are you doing here?!</i>

379
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:25,052
<i>Kyle?</i>

380
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:28,430
<i>We know you were here in</i>
<i>Amurao the night she was killed!</i>

381
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:30,057
<i>Did you kill her?</i>

382
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:33,602
[suspenseful music playing]

383
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,729
- [grunts]
- [muffled scream]
